text: The pictorella mannikin (Heteromunia pectoralis) (also known as the pictorella munia or pictorella finch) is a species of bird in the family Estrildidae. They live in northern Australia, from the Fitzroy River in Western Australia, across the "Top End" of the Northern Territory, over to the Cape York Peninsula. ==References== * * (2007a): [ 2006-2007 Red List status changes ].
